Tags.string 'NodeComment': Add a collectable to the list of collectables that are left on the map. Done by the game instance at the first start when no save game exists.

The level save object contains the data and functions. This object is than saved into a slot as a file on disc. If we would have several levels we could have a save game for each seperatly.

The game instance handles the save game data.
Get all the collectables (in our case only orbs) that are still in the map
Remove a collectable from our list of collectables that are still in the map. This uses an own struct we created that has the class and actor transform so we can place it at level start.
